      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CARDS NIGHT (1) used the inside draw to advantage last time and hit the ground running with a fast early split, but could manage only the minor money when a 5.5 lengths third at Ballarat over 390m in 22.51. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Can measure up this time. WHO SHE RULES (6) turned in a moderate performance last time when seventh at this track over 425m behind Oklahoma Bale (24.83) in a Mix 6/7. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Should be in this for a long way. GREYSYND BONNIE (8) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (28.65) at this track behind Kunama Namadgi in a Bottom Up - Grade 6. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expected to feature again. BERRINGA BLACK (2) is a last-start placegetter who is in the mix again.",
